CBRE is delighted to present, 1 Wurundjeri Drive, Epping, for sale via Expressions of Interest closing Thursday 21st November 2019 at 4pm (AEDT).

This outstanding building is strategically located within Northpoint Enterprise Park just off Cooper Street and within minutes of the Hume Freeway interchange, providing excellent access to all major road arterials.

The property includes ample production and laboratory facilities and is TGA compliant, highly suitable to beverage/liquid manufacturers (STCA).

Lease Details:
+ Lessee: Cold Drip Beverage Group Pty Ltd
+ Term: Five (5) years
+ Commencement date: 1st  July 2019
+ Options: Two, five (5) year options
+ Rental: $320,000 pa (plus GST & outgoings)

Property features:
+ Total building area: 1,603sqm*
+ Two  level office/amenity: 216sqm*
+ Town planning approval for an additional office/factory of 1,263sqm*
+ Multiple HVAC controlled production areas
+ Three (3) phase power - 250amps per phase
+ 2x container height roller shutter doors
+ Full staff amenity including lunchroom, male & female bathrooms plus shower
+ Gas and high power available within the estate

FOR SALE VIA EXPRESSIONS OF INTEREST CLOSING THURSDAY 21ST NOVEMBER 2019 AT 4PM (AEDT).

*approx.

CBRE Australian Healthcare & Social Infrastructure are proud to exclusively present 1/500 High Street, Epping – A premium healthcare and essential service investment leased to first-class convents; ASX listed Slater & Gordon and Capital Radiology, Australia’s leading imaging operator.

+ Premium healthcare and essential service investment leased to first-class convents including ASX listed Slater & Gordon and Capital Radiology - Australia’s leading imaging operator with 50+ locations

+ Highly exposed and trafficked location positioned within the booming Epping Homemaker Centre featuring, Chemist Warehouse, BCF, Mega Pet Warehouse and located adjacent McDonalds

+ Activity Centre zoned landholding of 1,606,sqm* across 3 (three) frontages totalling 113.2m*

+ Modern and imposing improvements with a highly specialised and capital-intensive medical fit out in-place for Capital Radiology

+ Prominent corner street frontage to 20,000 cars per day and with Pacific Epping only 500m* away -including, Coles, Woolworths Aldi, Big W, Best & Less, Target, Harris Scarfe, JB Hi-Fi and a Reading Cinema

+ Position at the centre of the City of Whittlesea, one of the fastest growing municipalities in Australia welcoming an average of 156 new residents and 76 babies every week

EXPRESSIONS OF INTEREST CLOSED - OFFERS UNDER REVIEW
